<br>
I've heard and noticed that two handed weapons deal more damage per second than two one handed weapons of similar quality. I've asked around about this and every where I ask I'm told that this is true...<br>
<br>
So my question is, Why do I never see Rangers using two handed weapons? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~Gatsu Bloodbourne, Mercenary in the service of Clan Twisted.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family: times new roman;font-size:x-small;">I long ago decided that I cared nothing for the trappings of good and evil.<br>
The petty politics made me sick<br>
Im a warrior and I deal in war<br>
War is neither good nor evil for it will claim one side as fast as the other<br>
Perhaps I'm a beast and a degenerate...but to be honest I care not.<br>
Because at the end of the day, I'll be the one with a three course meal and a warm bed.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> <br>
<br>
