Warlord of Cabilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjond>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1691<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/02 8:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You generally won't see ..</span><hr size=1> .. a big DPS gain from using 2H until you're 60 and you get triple attack.  Triple attack is potentially +50% to 2H DPS (3:2) while it's only potentially +25% for 2x1H (5:4) -- triple attack only works on the primary hand.<br>
<br>
Rangers, rogues, and monks have higher dual-wield skill caps than warriors, too.  This means their off-hand weapon swings more often.  DW skill determines whether or not the off-hand swings; off-hand delay determines how often the DW skill is checked.  Rangers and rogues have epics that give 40% haste, too.  They like to wield these in the off hand.  IIRC, rogues can't BS with a 2H piercer and the 2H weapons a ranger can even use aren't very nice.<br>
<br>
Monks are pretty much in the same boat as warriors wrt. 1H v. 2H.  They have different weapons available to them, but the choice doesn't obviously switch to 2H until 60+.  If you really want to be sure you're using the most damaging configuration, you'll need to parse your log file.  For Bjond at 53 now (monk), it's 1H.  I'm certain that will change at 60, though, based on my experience with my lizard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thewthunderstrike>ThewThunderstrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/10/02 4:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You generally won't see ..</span><hr size=1> <br>
